\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 5G technology represents the next generation of mobile networks, offering significantly faster data speeds, lower latency, and greater capacity compared to its predecessors. This technology is essential for supporting the growing number of connected devices and the increasing demand for high-bandwidth applications such as video streaming, online gaming, and virtual reality. 5G networks utilize higher frequency bands and advanced antenna technologies to achieve these improvements. The deployment of 5G is expected to drive innovation in various sectors, including autonomous vehicles, smart cities, and remote healthcare, by enabling real-time data transmission and enhanced connectivity.}